+# Chad media plan — JAG Electric
+
+Status: early media_plan only. No spend authorized. No ad account, CRM, website, tracking, or public asset mutations made.
+
+## Target geography
+
+Primary service radius:
+- Pittsburg, KS and nearby communities within roughly 30 miles.
+- Business base: Galena, KS.
+
+Initial paid geography recommendation:
+- Radius around Pittsburg, KS, with Galena included.
+- Keep radius conservative until lead quality is proven.
+- Do not overclaim every nearby town as a verified top market.
+
+Priority local pages to align with campaigns:
+- /service-area/pittsburg-ks
+- /service-area/galena-ks
+- /service-area/joplin-mo
+- /service-area/frontenac-ks
+- /service-area/girard-ks
+
+Notes:
+- Joplin, MO can be tested because it is in the site route list, but launch copy should not imply it is the highest-volume market unless JAG confirms that.
+- Avoid emergency or 24/7 geography/service messaging. Use “call to schedule” and “limited evening/weekend appointments” only.
+
+## Working hypotheses
+
+H1 — Trust-first local electrician demand:
+- Homeowners who need panel, wiring, outlet, fixture, or remodel electrical work will respond best to a trust-first message backed by verified reputation signals.
+- Proof available: 4.9 Google rating with 50 reviews supplied by Toby, 100% Facebook recommendation based on 20 reviews, BBB A+ accredited, HomeAdvisor 4.9 from 45 reviews.
+- Win condition before scaling: qualified calls or estimate-prep submissions at a sustainable cost, with project type and service area captured.
+
+H2 — Panel upgrades and remodel/new-construction jobs produce higher-intent leads than broad “electrician near me” messaging:
+- Panel upgrades, wiring, remodels, new construction, and commercial service are more concrete needs than generic electrician awareness.
+- Test service-specific campaigns before broad local branding spend.
+- Win condition: higher conversion rate and clearer project-fit notes than broad local ads.
+
+H3 — Pittsburg-area homeowners need a low-friction path from “I have an electrical issue” to “I know what to ask when I call”:
+- The estimate-prep page can reduce friction if positioned as a fast call-prep tool, not a fake automated quote engine.
+- Win condition: users submit enough detail for JAG to prioritize follow-up, or click-to-call from the estimate-prep path.
+
+H4 — Premium electrical visual identity can cut through local contractor sameness:
+- The dark graphite / electric cyan / copper conductor direction should be used in creative to make JAG memorable without cheesy lightning gimmicks.
+- Win condition: above-baseline CTR and click quality versus plain stock-contractor creative.
+
+## Channels
+
+Phase 0 — pre-launch / no spend:
+- Website route readiness check by Forge/Craig.
+- Tracking readiness check.
+- Creative asset inventory.
+- Organic/reputation alignment where available.
+
+Phase 1 — paid search intent test, after approval:
+- Google Search Ads for high-intent service terms.
+- Best fit for urgent/local electrician intent without making 24/7 claims.
+- Campaign groups should map to service pages:
+  - Panel upgrades
+  - Rewiring
+  - Lighting / fixtures
+  - Outlets / switches
+  - Remodel / new construction
+  - Commercial electrical
+
+Phase 2 — Meta local trust and retargeting test, after approval:
+- Facebook/Instagram local radius ads.
+- Best fit for visual trust, homeowner reminders, and retargeting site visitors.
+- Use reputation, service-area circuit board mechanic, and estimate-prep CTA.
+- Avoid fake project imagery or implying stock images are JAG jobs.
+
+Phase 3 — retargeting, after tracking proof:
+- Retarget website visitors and estimate-prep starters if Meta Pixel/Google tags are verified.
+- Message sequence:
+  - Trust proof
+  - Service-specific reminder
+  - Call-to-schedule / estimate-prep nudge
+
